changeSet.author: root
changeSet.sql: CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS PROJECT DEFAULT CHARACTER SET utf8 ; USE PROJECT;

changeSet.author: root
changeSet.sql: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `project`.`department` ( `ID` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, `DATE_OF_FORMATION` DATE NULL, `COMMON_INFO` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `MISSION` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `PURPOSE` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `DEPARTMENT_NAME` VARCHAR(255) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`)) ENGINE = InnoDB DEFAULT CHARACTER SET = utf8;

changeSet.author: root
changeSet.sql: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `project`.`emailaddress` ( `ID` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, `EMAIL` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `EMAIL_CATEGORY` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `EMPLOYEE_ID` VARCHAR(255) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`)) ENGINE = InnoDB DEFAULT CHARACTER SET = utf8;

changeSet.author: root
changeSet.sql: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `project`.`employee` ( `ID` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, `DATE_OF_BIRTH` DATE NULL, `DATE_OF_EMPLOYMENT` DATE NULL, `NAME` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `PATRONYMIC` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `SURNAME` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `DEPARTMENT_ID` VARCHAR(255) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`)) ENGINE = InnoDB DEFAULT CHARACTER SET = utf8;

changeSet.author: root
root
changeSet.sql: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `project`.`position` ( `ID` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, `NAME` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `PURPOSE` VARCHAR(255) NULL, `EMPLOYEE_ID` VARCHAR(255) NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`ID`)) ENGINE = InnoDB DEFAULT CHARACTER SET = utf8;
